          "@type": "Question",
          name: "What are the paid Stocky alternatives in 2026?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "The paid Stocky alternatives most-cited by independent reviewers in 2026: Qoblex (multi-channel inventory and procurement, ~$49-$249/mo), SKUSavvy (mobile-first warehouse management, ~$99-$499/mo), Sumtracker (bundles and kits, ~$49-$199/mo), Inventory Planner by Sage (advanced forecasting, ~$249-$999/mo), Cin7 Core (multi-warehouse, ~$349+/mo), and Prediko (AI demand forecasting, ~$119-$499/mo). Stocky Swap is positioned for stores wanting order logging at $0 rather than full inventory accounting." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "Can Stocky Swap import my historical Stocky data?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "Stocky Swap is a forward-only logger — it begins recording orders from the moment you switch it on. To preserve historical Stocky data, export your purchase orders, stocktakes, and supplier records from inside Stocky before the August 31 2026 shutdown. The Stocky data export guide on Stack Architect walks through what to save and how." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "Does Stocky Swap handle refunds, returns, or multi-location stock?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "Stocky Swap is built as a forward-only order ledger — it logs every new paid Shopify order. For full inventory accounting that handles refunds, returns, and multi-location stock movements, pair Stocky Swap with native Shopify Admin inventory tracking (which manages stock-on-hand correctly across these scenarios), or use the Stack Architect Pro bundle which includes additional Make.com scenarios for refund and return handling." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "What if my store outgrows the Make.com free tier?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "Make.com's free tier covers 1,000 operations per month. When your order volume requires more, Make.com's Core plan starts at $9 per month for 10,000 operations — still significantly cheaper than any paid Shopify inventory app. The same Stocky Swap scenario continues to run on the higher tier without modification." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "Is Stocky Swap better than the native Shopify inventory tools?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "They serve different purposes. Native Shopify Admin inventory handles stock-on-hand, transfers between locations, and basic receiving — and that's already free. Stocky Swap adds an independent, externally-owned audit log of every order in a Google Sheet you control — useful for finance reconciliation, accountant handoff, custom reporting, and as insurance against future Shopify changes. Most Shopify stores benefit from running both: native inventory for stock control, Stocky Swap for the order ledger." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "How do I migrate from Stocky to Stocky Swap?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "Migration takes three phases. First, export Stocky's historical data (purchase orders, stocktakes, supplier records) before any export functions are restricted. Second, deploy Stocky Swap and run it in parallel with Stocky for at least two weeks to verify orders are logging correctly. Third, after verification, you can switch off Stocky's daily use and rely on Stocky Swap as your forward order ledger. The full migration playbook is on the Stack Architect Stocky shutdown page." }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          name: "What is the cheapest Stocky alternative for Shopify?",
          acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: "Stocky Swap at $0 per month is the cheapest Stocky alternative for Shopify in 2026. It runs on Make.com's free tier with no Stack Architect fees. The next cheapest paid options start at approximately $9 per month for Make.com Core (if you outgrow free) or around $49 per month for entry-tier paid Shopify inventory apps like Qoblex or Sumtracker." }
        },
