  <section class="section">
    <div class="inner-md body-text">
      <div class="sec-head">
        <h2>What Stocky Swap does — and doesn't — do</h2>
        <p>The honesty section. Read this before deploying.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="speakable-limits">
      <h3>What it does</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Logs every paid Shopify order</strong> to a Google Sheet row in real time (order ID, timestamp, customer, SKU, product, quantity, revenue, fulfilment status)</li>
        <li><strong>Runs via Shopify webhook</strong> — not polling, so updates arrive within seconds of an order being placed</li>
        <li><strong>Stores data in your Google Sheet</strong> — full ownership, no vendor lock-in, exportable any time</li>
        <li><strong>Costs $0</strong> on <a href={MAKE_AFFILIATE} target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Make.com's free tier</a></li>
        <li><strong>Runs alongside Stocky</strong> until the August 31 shutdown — verify it's working in parallel before relying on it</li>
        <li><strong>Compatible with all Shopify plans</strong> — Basic, Shopify, Advanced, Plus, Starter</li>
        <li><strong>Re-deployable across multiple stores</strong> — clone the same scenario per store, point each to a separate sheet or tab</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What it does NOT do</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Backfill historical Stocky data</strong> — it logs forward from the moment you switch it on. Export your Stocky purchase orders, stocktakes, and supplier records separately before the shutdown.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculate stock-on-hand with refund/return adjustments</strong> — it's a forward order ledger, not an accounting system. For full inventory accounting, rely on native Shopify Admin inventory or pair with a paid alternative.</li>
        <li><strong>Manage purchase orders or supplier workflows</strong> — Stocky's strongest feature. If POs are critical to your operation, you need Qoblex, Inventory Planner, or similar.</li>
